                            <comment id="17819548" author="smiklosovic" created="Thu, 22 Feb 2024 09:35:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is even in 3.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=cassandra.git;a=tree&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=cassandra.git;a=tree&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;redirects to github and it 404&apos;s there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am not sure why we are even using these gitbox urls anymore, is this something &quot;official&quot; so we just remove &quot;;a=tree&quot; or should we just completely transition to github links?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(for the simplicity and minimizing the chances to mess things up, I am OK with gitbox links too)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17819604" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 22 Feb 2024 11:38:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s official but it used to have gitweb or something running there and now it looks like everything redirects, perhaps poorly.  I think cutting out the middle man and going directly to github makes sense at this point; we can always change it later if needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17819628" author="smiklosovic" created="Thu, 22 Feb 2024 12:11:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That brings another question - if we shoudn&apos;t change everything in &amp;lt;scm&amp;gt; to github too. I think that if it redirects that is just fine to keep it like it is. It would be different if there is some plan to completely deprecate gitbox and this redirection is just some kind of a transition towards that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17819681" author="michaelsembwever" created="Thu, 22 Feb 2024 15:03:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;gitbox is the official and permanent git url for the project (i.e. controlled on ASF Infra).&lt;br/&gt;
GitHub is a sync&apos;d convenience.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is encouraged to use GitHub though, it not just has the UI but handles load much better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820002" author="smiklosovic" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2024 10:07:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If it is official we should stick to it. Nothing wrong with removing &quot;;a=tree&quot; only.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will prepare all patches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820032" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2024 11:54:12 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is encouraged to use GitHub though, it not just has the UI but handles load much better.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This makes sense and I think we should switch the website to github for a better user experience.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820036" author="smiklosovic" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2024 12:10:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK so scm.url on github, all other links in scm on gitbox?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, should not we also reference a branch? E.g for 3.0 it would be like this: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&amp;lt;property name=&quot;scm.url&quot; value=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/tree/cassandra-3.0&quot;/&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It just feels weird to have a url which takes us to trunk in GH.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would be also visible in Maven pom&apos;s like here &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-3.0/build.xml#L311&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-3.0/build.xml#L311&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820038" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2024 12:20:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just the website to github.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820047" author="smiklosovic" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2024 12:59:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All PRs created.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820050" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2024 13:04:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems to be the opposite of changing the website?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820055" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2024 13:13:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Discussed offline, now I see, but I agree most with &apos;removing &quot;;a=tree&quot; only&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820067" author="smiklosovic" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2024 13:55:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;all prepared again&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820079" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 23 Feb 2024 15:04:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
